The paper deals with enhancing the expressiveness and representational capacity of recurrent neural networks (RNN) and explores stacked architectures with additional topological modifications like shortcut connections or bidirectionality. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-categories.
